The paper deals with the evaluation of compressibility parameters for random measures, which is a topic that falls under information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the evaluation of compressibility parameters for discrete-continuous measures, which is a topic that falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper further provides upper-bounds for the compressibility parameters, which is a topic that falls under numerical analysis (cs.NA) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
